ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How well do you think you did on the speech compared to other kids your age?
Notes: 1=The Worst; 2=Not Very Well; 3=About Average; 4=Pretty Well; 5=The Best

ElementDescription: How stressful was it to prepare the speech, knowing that you then had to give it in front of an audience?
Notes: 1=Not at all stressful; 2=A Little Stressful; 3=Somewhat Stressful; 4=Moderately Stressful; 5=Very Stressful

ElementDescription: How about during the speech, how stressful was it to be giving the speech in front of the video camera and panel of experts?
Notes: 1=Not at all stressful; 2=A Little Stressful; 3=Somewhat Stressful; 4=Moderately Stressful; 5=Very Stressful

ElementDescription: How about during the math part, how stressful was it to be doing subtraction in front of the video camera and panel of experts?
Notes: 1=Not at all stressful; 2=A Little Stressful; 3=Somewhat Stressful; 4=Moderately Stressful; 5=Very Stressful

ElementDescription: How did you cope with or handle the stress of preparing the speech and talking in front of the audience?
What did you do to stay calm and focused?
Pick a number from the third box, showing how well it worked (things they did to cope or stay calm and focused)
Notes: 1=Did Not Work at All; 2=Worked a Little; 3=Worked Ok; 4=Worked Pretty Well; 5=Worked Great

ElementDescription: Did you do things with your body like deep breathing to be calm?
Did you do things with your body like deep breathing to be calm? If yes, what did you do?
Pick a number from the third box, showing how well it worked (things with your body like deep breathing)
Notes: 1=Did Not Work at All; 2=Worked a Little; 3=Worked Ok; 4=Worked Pretty Well; 5=Worked Great

ElementDescription: Did you tell yourself calming or encouraging thoughts to stay calm?
Pick a number from the third box, showing how well it worked (calming or encouraging thoughts)
Notes: 1=Did Not Work at All; 2=Worked a Little; 3=Worked Ok; 4=Worked Pretty Well; 5=Worked Great

ElementDescription: What did you do in there? (Ask about materials in the room if silent)
What were you thinking about (If silent, probe if thinking about how well they did, what they could have said, etc.)
How were you feeling? (probe for sad, mad, embarassed, scared if silent)
Did you do anything in particular to make yourself feel better? Tell me everything you tried, whether it worked or not.
Pick a number from the third box, showing how well it worked (things they did to make self feel better).
Notes: 1=Did Not Work at All; 2=Worked a Little; 3=Worked Ok; 4=Worked Pretty Well; 5=Worked Great
